title: Queen (English automobile)
text: The Queen was an English <a href="automobile">automobile</a> produced from 1904 to 1905. "The car for the million or the millionaire", it was sold by Horner & Sons of <a href="Mitre%20Square">Mitre Square</a>, <a href="London">London</a>. Models of 12 and 16 hp were offered; prices ranged from 235 <a href="Guinea%20%28British%20coin%29">guinea</a>s to 275 guineas.
